The Collatz conjecture remains unproven as of 2025. No valid proof exists. Paul Erdős said "Mathematics is not yet ready for such problems." Terence Tao proved in 2019 that almost all positive integers (in a logarithmic density sense) eventually reach a value below any given function f(n) → ∞, but this falls short of proving convergence to 1 for all n. The conjecture has been verified computationally for all n up to roughly 2^68, but finite verification cannot substitute for a general proof. Any claimed proof you have seen is either flawed or a misrepresentation. I cannot produce a proof that does not exist.
